The tracking of these characters over a 12 year period is interesting and impressive, but the movie has gaping plot holes and character development that is either unexplained or unbelievable. Some of the characters are just caricatures kind of thrown up on the wall with no support or explanation. The actors who play the two leads, Ellar Coltrane and Lorelei Linklater, are one-dimensional actors in this movie and play very morose, seemingly depressed youth who drag themselves through life - they certainly don't demonstrate any joy for living. You can understand why Mason's high school girlfriend breaks up with him. Mom's two husbands go haywire with no development or warning, and this is especially jarring in the transformation of the second husband, who goes from being a very cool guy who is an understanding stepfather and husband to being someone's idea of a vet who goes bad. And how could Dad go from being a flaming liberal to finding happiness with the stereotyped bible-thumping, gun-toting Republican Texas family? In the end, the continuity of the actors is the thing, but the acting and plot development disappoints and leaves one feeling empty at the end.
