So, I rented BOYHOOD from Netflix, but they sent me this two hour forty five minute collection of outtakes. It seems there is no way to see the actual film, just these endless scenes that were deleted because they were so boring.

Apparently I have to have ten lines of text to post a review on IMDb. 

So, I'll recount some of the worst scenes. The scenes with Ethan Hawke singing singing  an unforgivable sin. The soundtrack songs (all of them, total crap). The Bible and Shotgun and Beatles album he gets for his fifteenth birthday. The scene where he's with a bunch of Jr and Sr High boys alone being dicks in an unfinished construction site. The scene where his drunk step-father is in the frame (all of them) His mother (every single second). The pointless scenes where he just whines and complains that life is pointless ( No, wait; the SCRIPT is pointless). Are we supposed to accept that he is a completely passive observer to his whole life, and gets into photography (ooooo a metaphor!) as a reflection of his mere observation of reality? Sorry, way too little, way too late. 

The gimmick filming the same cast as they age twelve yearsis nice. Too bad there wasn't a PLOT, Story, Action, or any point.

Total crap. Huge waste of time unless you're chief delight is The GOP and shooting guns and being a lower-middle class loser oxygen thief stuck in Nowhere, Texas. 

